<br>
I maxed out my points at the guildmaster and started researching my spells. I seemed to get about a 50% success rate except for that darn water pet which required about 5 tries (at 12pp a pop for the 20th level pet scroll). <br>
<br>
Practice research is pretty cool, at least at this level. When I hit 25 I used a backlog of practice runes I'd made (the ones that triv at 62) and got my five points with only seven pairs of runes, so practice research isn't nearly so heinous as something like tailoring. The only annoying part is getting all those goofy components, many of which don't stack. (Why on earth do sheets of parchment not stack??? They're paper, fer cryin' out loud!)<br>
<br>
Ice of Velious has been pretty easy for me to obtain just by fighting mobs and by finding it on vendors. Jade shards are common too, but I have a rough time finding pearl shards. <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 25th Trial<i><br>Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Kalamos</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(9/9/00 8:06:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Research</span><hr size=1> I agree whole heartedly with using skill points to increase your research level.  Sure it gets expensive at higher levels, but the practice items can end up costing you a fortune to get and a nice run all over Norrath.  Forget it ... I put my first point into research at lvl 24 (hint: that first point will give you the skill level of whatever your current char level is) and put all my saved points into it.  I researched the Fire, Water and Air pets as well as Everfount and Cornucopia with only one failure (luckily the failure came on Cornucopia ... a summon food scroll costs a lot less than the lvl 20 pet scrolls &quot;grin&quot;).  I plan to pour my next 20 skill points into research to do the lvl 29 spells when I get there.  So to sum it up ... I say forget practice research ... use your skill points, save older components to re-research spells you already have until it becomes trivial.  You can always sell the scroll to another Mage or simply give them away.  I've given research alot of thought and hae asked a lot of questions and have concluded that in the interests of enjoying the game (not running around looking for practice components) this is the best way.  There's my 2 copper.<br>
