<br>
Here's what he taught me, and it's worked well for me so far (having just hit lvl 29 and researched my Earth pet on the second try woohoo!!)<br>
<br>
1.  Buy your level 16 and level 20 pet spells at the Ocean of Tears merchant.  Overall, it's cheaper and less hassle than trying to research the pets.<br>
<br>
2.  Don't research until you absolutely have to.  Save all your practice points until you reach a level where you find a spell that you MUST have.  For me, that lvl was 24 and the spell was Everfount.<br>
<br>
3.  My mentor never used &quot;practice research&quot; - neither have I.<br>
<br>
4.  When grouped, offer to buy/trade mage words/components from others when they loot them.  Give necros the necro words you loot, give enchanters their pages, you get the idea.<br>
<br>
5.  CHECK MERCHANTS.  I've found Gloves of Rallos Zek, Flame of Vox, etc. on merchants along with a few mage words as well.  Not to mention finding cyclops toes, gargoyle eyes, etc. that are components for the mage focus items.<br>
<br>
Good luck! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> ICEHOUES</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(9/19/00 7:49:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   CAN U HELP ME OUT???</span><hr size=1> I AM NEW AT USING MY MAGE.  I AM LEL 15 NOW AND WILL BE LEL 16 SOON.  I DO NOT REALLY UNDERSTAND HOW TO DO RECEAECH.  I KNOW YOU HAVE TO FIND WORD AND COMBIND THEM, BUT THAT IS ALL I REALLY KNOW.  IF U CAN, CAN U PLEAES EXPLAIN HOW TO START DOING RESERECH. <br>
