<br>
I begin to hate research with growing passion every new spell level. At 29, Air and Fire pets are on vendors, and the 24 Earth pet is also on a vendor, so that one is also easily researched. At 29, the only pet requiring a researched spell as a research component is the water pet.<br>
<br>
So I saved up a batch of words of dimension and ice of velious and trotted out to the merchant in OOT. Bought a stack of level 20 water pets and started creating a pile of 24 water pet scrolls. I had hoped this would count as practice so I wouldn't need to spend money or skill points. But no, at level 30 the 24 water pet is trivial to research. &lt;sigh&gt; <br>
<br>
Apparently, if you want to raise your research skill by doing actual research, you have to research spells of your current circle. The research components for these, of course, only drop from mobs that con white or higher to you.<br>
<br>
The other night I paid a player 20pp to get 1 words of coercion and 1 flame of vox, neither of which have I ever seen drop off anything. Since components are turning out so expensive and hard to obtain, I've almost always found a high level mage to hit the combine button for me.<br>
<br>
So why am I raising my research skill? I don't dare make them myself, since I stand a great chance of losing my components. I guess I raise my skill so that I can combine spells for lower level mages. <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 30th Trial<i><br>Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Nathrak</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(9/29/00 2:47:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   research</span><hr size=1> I too had trouble with those lvl 24 spells, failing 5 times to make my pet (bad luck I guess, research maxed for level)<br>
<br>
That's when a movie line came back to me<br>
&quot;I have always relied upon the kindness of strangers&quot;<br>
<br>
Preparing for your new pets:<br>
<br>
The time to start preparing for your new pets is not when you are almost ready to ding or after.  At the very least, start a full spell circle before you need them. ie. You just ding 24, start looking for lvl 29 words and components.  Like to plan in advance, then print a list of every word you'll need and collect them for any level whenever you find them.<br>
(This works for those that don't have guildmates to help. If you have friends that are willing, let em know what you need)<br>
<br>
Researching those new pets:<br>
<br>
I collected all my components for a pet and put them into the research book.  In Kunark Firona Vie bank I saw a high level mage.  Being respectful of his time, I had everything ready to go, and asked him if his research skills were good if he would mind hitting the combine button for me.<br>
<br>
I've done this 3 times now with great luck. If you aren't begging words, are already pre-loaded and asking someone for 30 secs of their time, most everyone will be happy to help a fellow mage out.<br>
(note: make sure in your haste to preload your research book, you get the right components in. I screwed up once and lost everything because I hadn't put the right ones in. doh!) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udunedin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dunedin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(10/6/00 1:37:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Research</span><hr size=1> a nice place to find components is High Keep,  i have gotten a couple of Flame of Vox's,  3 ice of Velious and various words like Tyranny, Trancendence.  if you go there you will find a lot of the words and components you are looking for for the lower to mid level spells<br>
