<br>
Even so, research is easier now for a mage than it used to be.  The spells in Katta are huge -- not having to chain research your level 49 pet is a major bonus.<br>
<br>
There have always been rumors about vendors that sell mage research components.  I've chased more than a few, only to find out that it was just luck that someone sold a component to a vendor.  The dwarf vendors in OOT and Dagnor's Cauldron are examples of these... remember that the dwarves on Sister Isle are prime mage camp sites, and that Ice of Velious isn't used past 24 except for chain research... many mages dump their components once they don't need it, and that dwarf is the closest vendor.<br>
<br>
Level 16 and 20 pet spells can be bought from the high elf on the AC isle.<br>
<br>
Level 34 research pets CANNOT be bought from Katta... they are no longer there.  Verified as of 4/20/2002.  One Level 39 research pet CAN be bought there -- think it's water, but don't quote me.  All level 44 pets are there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=outofmana>OutOfMana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#333333>(12/6/02 12:35:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Finding HL words and components</span><hr size=1> For what it is worth, check out the merchants in the bank in Jaggedpine Forest.<br>
<br>
There are a lot of 50+ characters hunting this zone who no longer need these things and they often dispose of them to the merchants by the bank.  There are enough HL mobs that many of the things you need will be there.<br>
<br>
If you are really lucky, there will be a HL mage exping on gnolls or dryads who will do the combine for you.  Personally, I'm always willing to hit the combine button if someone hands me the book with the components in it (research about 180 from memory). <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showMessageRange?topicID=10.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showPrevMessage?topicID=10.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showNextMessage?topicID=10.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=40><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.threadControl?topicID=10.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=10.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=10.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value